### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### evnx-server API Tests
### VS Code: Install "REST Client" extension, then click "Send Request" above each ###
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@base_url = http://localhost:8080
@test_email = test@evnx.dev

### ── Health ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health Check
GET {{base_url}}/health

### ── Authentication ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register (use real evnx-crypto output for production)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{test_email}}",
  "srp_verifier": "",
  "srp_salt": "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=",
  "argon2_salt": "BBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBB",
  "ed25519_public_key": "CCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCC",
  "x25519_public_key": "DDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDD",
  "encrypted_private_key": "EEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE"
}

### Duplicate email → 409
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{test_email}}",
  "srp_verifier": "",
  "srp_salt": "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=",
  "argon2_salt": "BBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBB",
  "ed25519_public_key": "CCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCC",
  "x25519_public_key": "DDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDD",
  "encrypted_private_key": "EEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE"
}

### SRP Init — login step 1
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/srp/init
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{test_email}}",
  "client_public": ""
}

### SRP Init — unknown email (same shape expected, no user enumeration)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/srp/init
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nobody@doesnotexist.com",
  "client_public": ""
}

### SRP Verify — paste real session_id from srp/init response
# Replace SESSION_ID with the actual UUID from srp/init response
# This will return 401 with fake proof — use CLI for real login
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/srp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "SESSION_ID_FROM_INIT_RESPONSE",
  "client_proof": "aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa"
}

### Get Profile (requires valid JWT — paste from evnx auth login output)
# Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with real token from: evnx auth login
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Refresh Token
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

### Logout
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### ── TOTP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### TOTP Setup (requires valid JWT)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/totp/setup
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### TOTP Confirm (use code from authenticator app after scanning QR)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/totp/confirm
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "totp_code": "123456"
}

### ── Vaults ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List Vaults
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### List Vaults — No Auth → 401
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults

### Create Vault
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "myapp",
  "environment": "production",
  "encrypted_vault_key": "EEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE",
  "eph_pub_key": "FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF"
}

### Get My Vault Key — replace VAULT_ID
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults/VAULT_ID/my-key
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Delete Vault — replace VAULT_ID
DELETE {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults/VAULT_ID
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### ── Versions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Push Version — replace VAULT_ID
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults/VAULT_ID/versions
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nonce": "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA",
  "ciphertext": "BBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBB",
  "blob_hash": "aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "key_names": ["DATABASE_URL", "API_KEY", "DEBUG"],
  "key_count": 3,
  "base_version": 0
}

### List Versions — replace VAULT_ID
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults/VAULT_ID/versions
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Get Latest Version — replace VAULT_ID
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults/VAULT_ID/versions/latest
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### ── API Tokens ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List API Tokens
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/tokens
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Create API Token
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/tokens
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "ci-github-actions",
  "scope": "read",
  "expires_in_days": 90
}

### Revoke API Token — replace TOKEN_ID
DELETE {{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/tokens/TOKEN_ID
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Use API Token (evnx_tok_...) to list vaults
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/vaults
Authorization: Bearer evnx_tok_YOUR_RAW_TOKEN

### ── Users ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get Public Key for Vault Sharing
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/users/test@evnx.dev/public-key
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN